The Herald Blessings Chidakwa Municipal Reporter Illegal vendors have trooped back around Mupedzanhamo Market area in Mbare, Harare, encroaching the road servitude and causing congestion. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-559797" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/07/WhatsApp-Image-2021-07-14-at-11.17.09.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/07/WhatsApp-Image-2021-07-14-at-11.17.09.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/07/WhatsApp-Image-2021-07-14-at-11.17.09-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
A visit at the site this morning showed that the illegal traders, mostly selling second hand clothes bales, commonly referred to as mabhero were displaying their wares while encroaching on both the road and its servitude. Some of the traders were also not wearing face masks and there was no social distancing.